rune-desc-basic = A sinister rune used by sinister individuals for persorming sinister rituals.
rune-desc-malf = A senseless rune written in gibberish. No good can come from invoking this.
rune-desc-offering = Offers a noncultist above it to Nar'Sie, converting them. Requires 2 invokers.
rune-desc-sacrifice = Offers a noncultist above it to Nar'Sie, sacrificing them. Requires 3 invokers.
rune-desc-empower = Allows cultists to prepare greater amounts of blood magic at far less of a cost.
rune-desc-teleport = Warps everything above it to another chosen teleport rune.
rune-desc-revive = Requires a dead, mindless, or inactive cultist placed upon the rune. For each three bodies sacrificed to the dark patron, one body will be mended and their mind awoken.
rune-desc-barrier = When invoked, makes a temporary invisible wall to block passage. Can be invoked again to reverse this.
rune-desc-summon = Summons a single cultist to the rune. Requires 2 invokers.
rune-desc-bloodboil = Boils the blood of non-believers who can see the rune, rapidly dealing extreme amounts of damage. Requires 3 invokers.
rune-desc-spirit = Manifests a spirit servant of the Geometer and allows you to ascend as a spirit yourself. The invoker must not move from atop the rune, and will take damage for each summoned spirit.
rune-desc-apocalypse = A harbinger of the end times. Grows in strength with the cult's desperation - but at the risk of... side effects.
rune-desc-narsie = Tears apart dimensional barriers, calling forth the Geometer. Requires 9 invokers.

